The '''Anti-Corruption Commission Seychelles''' (abbreviated '''ACCS''') is an independent Seychellois [[government agency]] formed under the Anti-Corruption Act 2016.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.seychellesnewsagency.com/articles/4976/The+creation+of+an+Anti-Corruption+Commission+responds+to+a+request+of+the+Seychellois+people,+says+finance+minister|title=‘The creation of an Anti-Corruption Commission responds to a request of the Seychellois people,’ says finance minister|first=|last=|date=|website=seychellesnewsagency.com|accessdate=16 July 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.seychellesnewsagency.com/articles/4717/Seychelles+aims+to+strengthen+action+against+graft+with+new+Anti-Corruption+Commission#sthash.202fnTH9.dpuf|title=Seychelles aims to strengthen action against graft with new Anti-Corruption Commission|author1=Rassin Vannier|author2=Sharon Uranie|date=|website=seychellesnewsagency.com|accessdate=16 July 2017}}</ref> Formed in March 2016 after the [[National Assembly (Seychelles)|National Assembly]] enacted the "Anti-Corruption Law No. 6 of 2016",<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.seychellesweekly.com/2016/September%2021,%202016/soc1aa_anti-corruption_commision.html|title=Anti-Corruption Commission soon to start receiving public complaints|work=The Nation|via=Seychelles Weekly|date=30 September 2016|accessdate=16 July 2016}}</ref> the agency is charged with receiving complaints, investigating, detecting and preventing [[corruption]]-related practices in [[Seychelles]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.seychellesnewsagency.com/articles/7524/Head+of+Seychelles+anti-corruption+body+We+will+work+without+fear+or+favour|title=Head of Seychelles’ anti-corruption body: We will work without fear or favour|work=[[Seychelles News Agency]]|last=Ernesta|first=Sharon|date=5 July 2017|accessdate=16 July 2017}}</ref>
