{{Use dmy dates|date=January 2017}}{{Use British English|date=January 2017}}{{Infobox Railway Depot | name = Carlisle Kingmoor Marshalling Yard | location = [[Carlisle, Cumbria]] | owner = [[Direct Rail Services|DRS]] | depotcode = KM (1975 -)<ref name="TRC">{{cite web|url=http://www.therailwaycentre.com/Resource_data/AllTimeShedCodes.pdf|title=The all-time guide to UK Shed and Depot Codes|date=5 May 2006|work=TheRailwayCentre.com|accessdate=19 August 2016|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131217221651/http://www.therailwaycentre.com/Resource_data/AllTimeShedCodes.pdf|archivedate=17 December 2013}}</ref> | type = [[Diesel Locomotive|Diesel]] }}
'''Carlisle Kingmoor Marshalling Yard''' is a [[stabling point]] located in [[Carlisle, Cumbria]], England. The depot is situated on the [[West Coast Main Line]] and is near [[Carlisle railway station|Carlisle station]].
== History == From 1950 to 1982, [[British Rail Class 03|Class 03]], [[British Rail Class 04|04]], [[British Rail Class 08|08]], [[British Rail Class 09|09 shunters]], [[British Rail Class 11|and Class 11]], [[British Rail Class 17|17]], [[British Rail Class 25|25]], [[British Rail Class 27|27]], [[British Rail Class 28|28]], [[British Rail Class 40|and 40 Diesel Locomotives]].<ref name=CKNYallocation1>{{cite web|url=http://www.brdatabase.info/sites.php?page=depots&subpage=locos&id=125|title=Locomotive Depots: Carlisle New Yard (Allocation)|work=BRDatabase|accessdate=1 January 2017}}</ref>
== Present == From 2013, the depot has no allocation. It is, instead, a stabling point for EWS [[British Rail Class 66|Class 66]] and Freightliner [[British Rail Class 70 (diesel)|Class 70 locomotives]].<ref name=CKNYallocation>{{cite web|url=http://travelandmixpix.smugmug.com/keyword/carlisle%20kingmoor/|title=travelmixpix Photo Keyword - Carlisle Kingmoor|work=SmugMug|accessdate=1 January 2017}}</ref>
