{{Expand German|Preußische Verfassung (1848/1850)|date=September 2013}}
The '''Constitution of Prussia''' ({{lang-de|Verfassungsurkunde für den preußischen Staat}}), was the first [[constitution]] of the [[Kingdom of Prussia]]. It was promulgated on 5 December 1848 by [[Frederick William IV of Prussia|Frederick William IV]], in response to the [[Revolutions of 1848 in the German states#Prussia|revolutions of 1848]]. Thereby committing himself to [[Unification of Germany|unification]] (i.e. the [[German question]]), forming a [[Liberalism|liberal]] [[government]] and convening a [[Prussian National Assembly|national assembly]].

==External links==
* [http://www.documentarchiv.de/nzjh/verfpr1848.html Text of the Constitution] {{De icon}}

