'''Dormeuil''' is a [[Economy of France|French]] [[textile]] company founded in 1842 by 22-year-old Jules Dormeuil.<ref>[http://www.dormeuil.com/en/about-us/history/ Dormeuil: history]</ref><ref>2012 Joel & Son Fabrics [http://www.joelandsonfabrics.com/uk/brands/dormeuil Dormeuil]</ref>
==History== Dormeuil began with importing English fabrics to France. By 1862 its headquarters were established at 4 rue Vivienne in [[Paris]].<ref>dormeuil.com [http://www.dormeuil.com/en/about-us/history/ History]</ref> The first shop outside France was located at 10 [[New Burlington Street]] in [[London]].
Dominic Dormeuil is the current President.<ref>[http://www.dormeuil.com/en/ Dormeuil]</ref>
==Locations== [[brand|Monobrand]] stores are located in [[Paris]], [[Neuilly sur Seine]], [[Bordeaux]], [[Strasbourg]] and [[Minato-ku, Tokyo]].<ref>[http://www.dormeuil.com/en/fashion/dormeuil-shops/ Dormeuil shops]</ref>
==See also== *[[Loro Piana]] *[[Holland & Sherry]] *[[Ermenegildo Zegna]] *[[Vitale Barberis Canonico]] *[[Scabal]]
