'''Khalaktyrskoye''' ({{lang-ru|Халактырское}}) is a lake on the eastern outskirts of the city [[Petropavlovsk-Kamchatsky]] in [[Kamchatka Krai]], Russia. It occupies an area of {{convert|2,2|km|mi|sp=us}}, maximum depth is 12,1 meters. Its main outflow is River Halaktyrka.

