[[File:Staatswappen-Liechtensteins.svg|thumb|right|150px|Coat of Arms of the Principality of Liechtenstein]]
This page lists diplomatic missions accredited to [[Liechtenstein]]. The Principality of Liechtenstein is, along with the Vatican City, one of only two sovereign states in the world without a resident embassy or consulate located within its territory. Eighty-six countries have ambassadors accredited to Liechtenstein, with most being resident in [[Bern]], [[Vienna]] or [[Berlin]].

